DIGEST
SB 347 Reengrossed 2026 Regular Session Barrow
Present law (17:3399.12) provides for the following definitions relative to the Campus
Accountability and Safety Act: "Chancellor", "Confidential advisor", "Employee",
"Institution", "Power-based violence", "Responsible employee", "System president", and
"Title IX coordinator".
Proposed law retains present law but changes the definition of "power-based violence" to
mean conduct intended to control, coerce, harm, exploit or intimidate another person on the
basis of sex through the assertion of power or authority.
Proposed law provides that "power-based conduct" includes any conduct prohibited by
present law providing for unlawful deepfakes and unlawful dissemination or sale of images
of another created by artificial intelligence, or any succeeding statue that involves media
generated by artificial intelligence or deepfake media depicting sexual imagery.
Present law (17:3399.16) provides that the administration of each institution must distribute
information to students regarding power-based violence, campus safety, internet and cell
phone safety, and online content that is a potential threat to school safety.
Proposed law retains present law and further provides that the administration must distribute
information not less than four times per academic year; delivered in-person, online, or both.
Effective upon signature of the governor or lapse of time for gubernatorial action.
(Amends R.S. 17:3399.12(5) and 3399.16(A), (B), and (C))
